  "commentary": "With SPX at 6765 sitting right at the max negative gamma strike (-42.7B), dealers are in maximum amplification mode and will aggressively buy any dip while selling rallies back toward the 6800 positive gamma wall (28.6B). The massive negative GEX concentration between 6750-6770 creates a highly unstable zone where any directional move gets amplified by dealer hedging flows. The recent GEX surge event combined with the breakout regime suggests we're primed for volatile, trending moves with 6800 acting as strong resistance where dealer selling intensifies.\n\nBottom line: expect wild swings with strong buying support on dips but heavy selling pressure if we push toward 6800.",
